               <p>JAMES ADAMS. I am the son of Edward Adams, who <rs id="t18180218-3-viclabel14" type="occupation">keeps the White Hart</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180218-3-victim62 t18180218-3-viclabel14"></join> at <placeName id="t18180218-3-crimeloc15">Crandford-bridge</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180218-3-crimeloc15" type="placeName" value="Crandford-bridge"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180218-3-crimeloc15" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180218-3-off12 t18180218-3-crimeloc15"></join>. On the 10th of December, I and Harvey concealed ourselves in the cart-yard; about two o'clock in the morning, I saw the prisoner go down the rick-yard, he returned in about ten minutes with a bag on his back, we seized him, and he threw it away-it contained nine saddle-skiris, which had been cut off the saddles.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180218-3-person65">
